      "text": [
        ": كَتَبَ إِلَيَّ أَبُو اَلْحَسَنِ اَلرِّضَا عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ «قُلْ فِي سَجْدَةِ اَلشُّكْرِ مِائَةَ مَرَّةٍ: شُكْراً شُكْراً وَ إِنْ شِئْتَ عَفْواً عَفْواً."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.970 - It is narrated from Sulayman ibn Hafs al-Marwazi that Imam al-Ridha (as) wrote to him, saying:\n“In the prostration of gratitude (Sajdat al-Shukr), say one hundred times:\n‘Thankfulness, thankfulness (Shukran, Shukran),’ and if you wish, say:\n‘Pardon, pardon (Afwan, Afwan).’”"
        ]
      }
    },
